<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-527] Update methods to remove OST in manual</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-527</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Lustre manual section 14.9.3: &quot;Removing an OST from the File System&quot; makes reference to using lctl llog_cancel, but the syntax it uses is wrong for at least lustre 2.12.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It says:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lctl --device MGS llog_cancel testfs-client -i 138&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But it should say:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lctl --device MGS llog_cancel --catalog testfs-client --log_idx 138&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The documented syntax appears to not exist in 2.12 nor 2.15.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
