                            <comment id="412156" author="JIRAUSER18900" created="Tue, 23 Apr 2024 12:24:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh. Well, I can&apos;t seem to fix my typo. Or add a description. Anyway...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lustre manual section 14.9.3: &quot;Removing an OST from the File System&quot; makes reference to using lctl llog_cancel, but the syntax it uses is wrong for at least lustre 2.12.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It says:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lctl --device MGS llog_cancel testfs-client -i 138&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But it should say:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lctl --device MGS llog_cancel --catalog testfs-client --log_idx 138&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The former syntax appears to no longer exist.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
